headline.main: MOULMEIN YIELDED; British Retreat to West Bank of Salween River, Barrier to Rangoon NO EQUIPMENT IS LOST Rear Guard Delays Foe -The Japanese Push Came 'From All Directions' A SETBACK FOR THE BRITISH IN BURMA MOULMEIN FALLS TO FOE IN BURMA

lead_paragraph: RANGOON, Burma, Jan. 31 -British defenders of the Burma Road evacuated the strategic port of Moulmein and fell back under a powerful Japanese enveloping attack today to establish strong new lines west of the deep, three-mile-wide Salween River, about ninety-two miles from Rangoon.
